SIMPLE: interrogate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interrogate
<hw>In*ter"ro*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interrogating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>interrogatus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>interrogare</ets> to ask; <ets>inter</ets> between +
<ets>rogare</ets> to ask. See Rogation.]</ety> <def>To question
formally; to question; to examine by asking questions; <as>as, to
<ex>interrogate</ex> a witness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wilt thou, uncalled, <qex>interrogate</qex>,⟦br⟧
Talker! the unreplying Fate?</q> <rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To question; ask. See
<er>Question</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interrogate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interrogate
<hw>In*ter"ro*gate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To ask questions.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interrogate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Interrogate
<hw>In*ter"ro*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
interrogation; a question.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interrogatee</ent>⟦br⟧
